File Photo  Two persons have been reported dead after a commercial vehicle plungedinto a river in Osun State.According to Folashade Odoro, the spokesperson for the Osun StatePolice Command, the accident happened at an area known as Oke-Gada inEde on Monday.One of the residents of the area said the accident happened around 7pm. He said the driver was trying to avoid potholes near the bridge onthe river.The occupants of the vehicle were said to have been rushed to aprivate hospital in the area.